      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;A DPS class is supposed to be crap solo in pvp. A utility class, though&amp;nbsp;able stay alive, is also crap in pvp.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Its when you combine the two in a pair, or more, that the classes unlock their potential.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A rogue alone won't kill much, but give him a bard to dispell his targets and selo him, and he is murderous.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A wizard solo can't take much punishment, but give him a shaman to malos his targets and heal him, and he'll see his full damage potential.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A lone magician isn't terribly dangerous, but give him an enchanter to dispell and tash while his hasted pet roots their target, and he is deadly.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;SOLO PVP IS ENTIRELY IRRELEVANT. Rogues and DS's fit perfectly into the scheme of pvp.&amp;nbsp;Too bad you need a partner to be effective, but welcome to Everquest.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
